  "title": "Class of 2024 Graduate Convocation",
  "description": "Jointly established by New York University and East China Normal University, NYU Shanghai is the third degree-granting campus in NYU’s global network, joining NYU Abu Dhabi and NYU's campus in New York City.",
  "language": "en",
  "published_time": "",
  "modified_time": "",
  "sitemap_lastmod": null,
  "text": "Class of 2024 Graduate Convocation\nNYU Shanghai held its fifth Graduate Convocation on May 26 to celebrate the graduation of 140 PhD and Master’s degree candidates from eight programs: Doctor of Philosophy in Mathematics, Doctor of Philosophy in Neural Science, Master of Arts in Teaching English to Speakers of Other Languages (TESOL), Master of Arts in Interactive Media Arts (IMA), Master of Science in Data Analytics & Business Computing (MSDABC), Master of Science in Quantitative Finance (MSQF) , Master of Science in Marketing and Retail Science (MSMRS), and Master of Science in Organization Management and Strategy (MSOMS). 300 family members and friends attended the convocation in person, in addition to those around the globe who watched via livestream, as 127 students walked across the stage in NYU Shanghai’s New Bund Campus auditorium to receive their degrees in person, and 13 graduates participated remotely.\nNYU Shanghai’s advanced degree Class of 2024 will continue their careers in a variety of industries and sectors. The PhD graduates will move on to institutions such as the Beijing Institute of Mathematical Sciences. NYU Shanghai - NYU Stern MS graduates have accepted offers from PricewaterhouseCoopers (PwC), Tiffany & Co., Adidas Sports (China) Co., Ltd., and Guotai Junan Securities, among others. Graduates of the TESOL program will continue to advance in their careers at educational institutions in China and around the world. IMA graduates’ thesis projects were on show from June 20-21 in the 3rd and 4th floor North Hall IMA studios on campus.\nWatch the 2024 Graduate Convocation highlight video:\nWatch the entire Convocation here.\nRead more about the Convocation here.\nNYU Shanghai 2024 Graduate Convocation Program\nClass of 2024 Graduate Convocation",
